  "doc_id": "431",
  "text": "The period inaugurating the first clear step into an \"icehouse\" world at the Eocene/Oligocene transition is much less well documented. In many Alpine orogeny related basins, the sedimentary changes of this period are often interpreted in terms of regional tectonics changes and to their proximity to the active orogen (e.g. [CITATION_1] . However, the last decades have seen the emergence of an increasing amount of evidence for a rich climatic history on a global scale during the early Cenozoic, allowing a better understanding of tectonic/climate relationships [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Thus, it is fundamental to investigate whether these early Cenozoic climatic events may have dominated the sedimentary record, where there is tectonic, even in the case of foreland basins.",
